<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Den1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Den,</orth> 1) a cave: <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.1.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. IV, 1, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.5.39" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B V, 5, 39</bibl>. Especially the habitation of a lion: <bibl n="shak. lll 4.1.95" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 1, 95</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.291" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 291</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.1.57" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.2.12" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 2, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.5.74" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 5, 74</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 5.1.17" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. V, 1, 17</bibl>.<lb />2) a pit: <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.215" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 215</bibl>.
<lb />3) a hollow, a glen: <bibl n="shak. tit 4.1.59" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 1, 59</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>